n both the subject block and an it/specify block. e.g.\n\n```\ndescribe \"Foo\" do\n  def my_helper\n    MyClass\n  end\n\n  subject { my_helper.new }\n  specify { my_helper.should do_something }\nend\n```\n\nThis code gives undefined method `my_helper' for #Rspec::Core::ExampleGroup... as the subject block is being evaluated in the context of the ExampleGroup class.\n\nIf an explicit subject is specified, it should be evaluated in the context of the ExampleGroup instance (this was the case for rspec-1).\n","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rspec/rspec-core/issues/17/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rspec/rspec-core/issues/17/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}